==Spanish==
===Etymology===
Latin ''[[aqua]]''
===Noun===
'''agua''' ''f''

#[[water]].
#:''el agua clara''

===Usage note===
''agua'' is a feminine noun in Spanish but, like other feminine nouns starting with a stressed ''a'' sound, it takes the masculine definite article, ''el''. It is nevertheless clearly feminine, as shown by the gender of adjectives.

